RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 19600. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEVERPOPTHECORK settled in the three path the opening turn, started a four wide bid approaching the three eighths pole and took the nod at the five sixteenths, rounded the far turn off the rail and held well under steady stretch handling. OFFICER STONE raced boxed in on the first turn, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole and improved in the four path of the far turn, then dueled through later yards for second. RED HOT TODDY stalked three wide on the first turn, took the nod toward the three eighths pole and dueled from that point, was met at the five sixteenths, came in a path past the pole then dropped back and flattened stride into the far turn. DE'S CASTLE stalked two deep then took the nod into the backstretch and dueled from that point, was forced in and had his heels clipped past the five sixteenths pole then faded off the rail on the far turn. IN HIGH GEAR stalked off the rail the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened approaching the far turn. HILLBILLY ROCK saved ground well off the pace, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, fell over MONKEY WRENCH past the five sixteenths pole but got up and walked off. The latter took the lead leaving the thirteen sixteenths pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was met into the backstretch and dueled from that point, but steadied while in tight quarters at the rail, clipped the heels of De's Castle and fell passing the five sixteenths pole, but got up and walked off. A Stewards inquiry resulted in the disqualification of Red Hot Toddy to fifth place for causing the incident leaving the five sixteenths pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Hillbilly Rock
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 3/8,fell over rival past 5/16,walked off

ENTRY.NAME: In High Gear
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,chased 7/16,weakened near far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Neverpopthecork
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled 3p,4wd bid near 3/8,up 5/16,off rail turn,steady urging

SILVER RULES rated off the early pace toward the inside, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the turn at the rail and dueled through the stretch for second. SPARKLEINYOUREYE gave chase and raced four wide through the turn, dug in leaving the turn and took the nod for third under the wire. LA MADDALENA engaged in close chase through the backstretch, remained a factor in the three path on the turn but relented in the duel through the stretch. OUR GREAT NOTION gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn then flattened. POLISH THE DIAMOND gave chase, rounded the turn five wide and showed little in the lane. IHEARTRAINACOMN broke a step slow then gave chase toward the inside, was eased to the six path on the turn and showed little in the lane.

THE CLOWN gave chase and raced at the rail into the turn, angled to the six path approaching the top of the lane, finished well and was gaining on the top two. GREAT GOOGLYMOOGLY was hustled to the lead inside and rated the pace from the three eighths pole, came under pressure nearing the quarter, raced at the rail on the turn, was met into the lane and flattened inside the sixteenth pole. BASHDAFLASH lunged and was steadied leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. FLASH OF DAY chased outside, raced in the six path on the turn and proved empty down the lane. RYE WHISKEY gave chase, rounded the turn about the five path then flattened in the lane. TRICKY STRONG chased through the backstretch, raced in the three path on the turn and weakened in the lane.

FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEVER COMPROMISE saved ground close to the early pace, picked up the chase leaving the half mile pole, moved to even terms two deep midway on the far turn and dug in under determined handling to inch clear. WHAT DOES IT TAKE took the lead leaving the three quarter pole and rated the pace inside, raced clear into the backstretch, was pressured past the three eighths, met at even terms midway on the far turn and dueled gamely to late stretch before reluctantly ceding. FIELDSTONE raced well back off the rail on the first turn, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole, circled rivals in the seven path on the far turn and came along for third late. NAPA VALLEY saved early ground, gave chase toward the three eighths pole and rounded the far turn about the three path, then flattened mid-stretch. GREAT DAYS AHEAD saved ground well off the early pace, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and weakened the final sixteenth. KRUG rounded the first turn about the four path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and showed little in the lane. MY MIRACLE MAN stalked three wide the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened approaching the far turn. AUBURN MILL rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn. ROYAL PAIN raced well back off the rail, gave chase from the three eighths pole but showed little response. SUBJECT TO CHANGE rated close in the three path the first turn then faded past the five sixteenths pole.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ICY STARE took over leaving the chute and rated the pace through the backstretch, was urged leaving the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the turn then steadily handled in the stretch. HOLY HIP chased the early pace toward mid track, rounded the turn near the rail and dueled through the stretch for second. TALENTED CORINNA tapered toward mid track and gave chase, raced in the three path on the turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for second. WEST COAST WILDCAT chased inside, raced off the rail on the turn, drifted into the stretch then flattened the final sixteenth. DAPPLESANDDIAMONDS steadied off the heels of Talented Corinna past the half mile pole then gave chase toward the outside, raced in the four path on the turn then flattened in the lane. FIDDLERSHOTPLEASUR gave chase, rounded the turn about the five path and showed little in the lane. MY BEST GIRL chased, angled to the seven path through the turn and passed tiring horses in the stretch. MOON WALKIN and PRINCESS MIA ROSE were not factors. ESTILO AMOROSO gave chase then weakened at the rail on the turn. The Stewards reviewed, then rejected, a claim of foul against the rider of Talented Corinna, for alleged interference shortly after the start, lodged by the rider of Dapplesanddiamonds.
